  "texts": [
    "C. Unified Loss Function for Two Collapse PhenomenaBuilding upon the posterior collapse phenomenon discussed in Section IV-B, we now present our unified approach to inducing both diffusion collapse and concentration collapse during VAE inference.",
    "Our method (shown in Fig. 2) leverages a single KL divergence-based loss function that can achieve both protection objectives through strategic parameter adjustment.Posterior-Collapse-phenomenon in VAEs' inference stage can manifest in two primary forms: diffusion collapse and concentration collapse.",
    "Both potential collapses could be induced in the inference stage, by maximizing and minimizing the KL divergence.",
    "Here we give definitions of two kind of collapses and explain when the phenomenon will occur.",
    "Let X be the input space and Z ⊆ R d be the latent space of a VAE."
  ]
}